<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1162">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/130.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Bevan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 634.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch
                            No. 1182 of August 14, 1914, enclosing a copy of a decree issued by
                            Governor Candido Aguilar of the State of Vera Cruz, Mexico, relative to
                            leasing oil lands in the State of Vera Cruz. The Department presumes
                            that the decree in question is intended to relate to future transactions
                            only. Inasmuch, however, as it does not appear entirely clear from the
                            language of the decree that such is the case, you are directed to make
                            an investigation and report on this point.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>